title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> be a field, let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A\in \mathop {\mathrm {Mat}}\nolimits _{n}(\mathbb {F})]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[n\times  n]]></fr:tex> matrix over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[c_{A}(x)=\det (x I_{n}-A)]]></fr:tex> be the <fr:link
type="local"
href="ela-001R.xml"
addr="ela-001R"
title="Characteristic polynomial of a matrix">characteristic polynomial</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>, and let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m_{A}(x)]]></fr:tex> be the <fr:link
type="local"
href="ra-0051.xml"
addr="ra-0051"
title="Minimal polynomial of a matrix">minimal polynomial</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>. Then the minimal polynomial of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> divides the characteristic polynomial for the matrix <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m_{A}(x)\mathrel {\bigm |} c_{A}(x)]]></fr:tex>. Moreover there exists an <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m\in \mathbb {N}]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[c_{A}(x)\mathrel {\bigm |} m_{A}(x)^{m}]]></fr:tex>, where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[m]]></fr:tex> is the number of <fr:link
type="local"
href="ra-0054.xml"
addr="ra-0054"
title="Invariant factors of a matrix">invariant factors</fr:link> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
